definition: Czech/Czech Republic/abbr. for 捷克[Jie2 ke4]
abbr. for 克羅地亞|克罗地亚[Ke4 luo2 di4 ya4], Croatia/(Tw) abbr. for 克羅埃西亞|克罗埃西亚[Ke4 luo2 ai1 xi1 ya4], Croatia

pinyin: Jie2 ke4 Si1 luo4 fa2 ke4

sentences.english: On Saturday, three people died in the German town of Neukirchen, near the Czech border.
sentences.chinese: 週六德國靠近捷克邊境城市紐克爾遜三人已經死亡。

sentences.english: Dr Gammans travelled to the Czech Republic to learn the method.
sentences.chinese: 加曼斯博士專程到捷克共和國去學習這個方法。
捷克人說的塞而維克語。

sentences.english: Czech, a member of the Slavic languages.
sentences.chinese: 捷克語，是斯拉夫語言的一種。

sentences.english: I want to help Slavia in the Czech league as well as in the Champions League qualification.
sentences.chinese: 我想幫助斯拉維亞隊在捷克聯賽中獲得歐冠參賽資格。

sentences.english: Czech Republic is second on 10 points, with Scotland on eight.
sentences.chinese: 捷克累積10分緊隨其後，而蘇格蘭則排名第八。

sentences.english: Each Czech drinks over 175 pints of beer a year on average.
sentences.chinese: 捷克平均每人每年喝酒175品脫。

sentences.english: Steam Whistle's Czech brewmaster asked for a bedroom at the brewery.
sentences.chinese: 公司的那位捷克裔釀酒大師就要求在廠裏置一間臥室。

sentences.english: The city became the capital of newly formed Czechoslovakia in 1918. Population, 1,189,828.
sentences.chinese: 1918年該城成爲新形成的捷克斯洛伐克的首都。

sentences.english: Poland and the Czech Republic were client states of the former USSR for many years.
sentences.chinese: 波蘭和捷克共和國多年來是前蘇聯的附庸國。

sentences.english: Besides, the two Prime Ministers also jointly met with representatives from the Czech business community on the evening of December 8.
sentences.chinese: 此外，兩國總理8日晚還共同會見了捷克工商界代表。

sentences.english: He didn't even know he was Czech.
sentences.chinese: 他甚至不知道自已是捷克人。

sentences.english: It was dominated by the Czechs of Bohemia.
sentences.chinese: 這是由捷克波希米亞爲主。

sentences.english: I also hope to be here to learn English a…
sentences.chinese: 同時我也希望能夠在這裏學習英文和捷克語。

sentences.english: Czech teen Vaidisova is looking for her first Grand Slam title.
sentences.chinese: 捷克小將瓦娃在期待她的第一個大滿貫。

sentences.english: Clinton met with Czech Republic Foreign Minister Karel Schwarzenberg, whose government - along with Poland - has agreed to host the system.
sentences.chinese: 捷克和波蘭政府同意在他們的國家部署導彈防禦系統。
